# Handoff — 2026-07-13 (Session 4, Pack #4)

## Resume point
Wire-format rename of the two LLM adapter crates is **code-complete, all
4 validation gates green, working tree staged for commit**. The user
wanted the misleading vendor name "OpenAiAdapter" / "afa-plugin-llm-
openai-compat" purged in favour of the actual protocol name (Responses
API for the new wire format, Chat Completions for the older wire
format). The rename is split into two atomic commits worth of work
(Phase 2 streaming + Phase 2.5 wire-format rename) but the user wants
a single commit.

## What's done

- `crates/afa-plugin-llm-openai-compat/` → `crates/afa-plugin-llm-chat-
  completions/` (12 file renames: 1 Cargo.toml + 4 examples + 4 src +
  3 tests, all tracked by git as `R`).
- `crates/afa-plugin-llm-http/src/openai_adapter.rs` →
  `crates/afa-plugin-llm-http/src/responses_adapter.rs` (1 file rename).
- Type renames in `afa-plugin-llm-http`:
  - `OpenAiAdapter` → `ResponsesAdapter`
  - `OpenAiConfig` → `ResponsesConfig`
  - `OPENAI_PROD_BASE_URL` → `OPENAI_RESPONSES_BASE_URL`
  - `map_request_to_openai` → `map_request_to_responses`
  - preset `gpt_4o` → `responses_gpt_4o` / `responses_gpt_4o_with_base_url`
  - module path `super::openai_adapter::` → `super::responses_adapter::`
  - tracing message "openai adapter recovered after 401" → "responses
    adapter recovered after 401"
  - All CID header comments + module doc-block stories rewritten to
    refer to "OpenAI Responses-API specialist" (accurate description,
    not a vendor tag)
- Type renames in `afa-plugin-llm-chat-completions`:
  - `OPENAI_CHAT_PROD_BASE_URL` → `OPENAI_CHAT_COMPLETIONS_BASE_URL`
  - default `provider_name` `"openai-prod"` → `"chat-completions-prod"`
  - example `SecretRef.name` `"openai-prod-key"` → `"chat-completions-
    prod-key"` (test fixtures)
  - test `SecretRef.name` `"openai-compat-test-key"` → `"chat-
    completions-test-key"` (test fixtures)
- Cross-crate sweep: `afa-contracts::llm::capabilities` (doc comment),
  `afa-llm::tests::llm_v1` (doc comment), `afa-llm::conformance` (the
  rename touched audit-event key names too).
- `Cargo.lock` regenerated (the renamed crate changed path in the
  workspace member hash).
- `cargo fmt --all` applied (the rename produced 3 long-line
  diagnostics that fmt cleaned up).
- `docs/features/llm-engine-baseline/{PRD,TRD,FLOW,IMPL}.md` updated
  to reflect the new crate + type names. (Docs live in
  `../docs/`, outside the `afa/` git repo, so the doc edits are NOT
  staged — they are local-only and the next commit on the docs
  branch can pick them up.)

## What's NOT done (intentional, out of scope)

- The `async-openai = "0.29"` dep is still in
  `crates/afa-plugin-llm-http/Cargo.toml` line 13. Per project
  memory, this is a leftover Phase 1 dependency scheduled for
  removal in Phase 3 cleanup. It is not used by any `use` in the
  crate (raw `reqwest` does the transport). Dropping it now would
  mix the wire-format rename with a dep-removal cleanup; the user
  asked for the rename only. Note for Phase 3.
- The session logs (`sessions/llm-engine-*.md`) and
  `sessions/.last-handoff` still reference the old names. Per the
  `log-prompt` skill rule "append only — never rewrite earlier
  entries", those are frozen historical records. Future agents
  should read the new commit message and the new handoff for the
  current names.

